items.abstract: <jats:p>Reduction of 2α-nitro-5α-cholestan-3-one (<jats:bold>4</jats:bold>), its enol tautomer (<jats:bold>3a</jats:bold>) and 3-acetylamino-2-nitro-5α-cholest-2-ene (<jats:bold>2</jats:bold>) was studied. The latter compound was reduced with zinc in acetic acid to 3β-acetylamino-5α-cholestan-2-one (<jats:bold>8</jats:bold>). The similar reaction of <jats:bold>3a</jats:bold> or <jats:bold>4</jats:bold> led to 2α-amino-5α-cholestan-3-one (<jats:bold>11a</jats:bold>), that may be trapped as <jats:italic>N</jats:italic>-formyl derivative. When crude <jats:bold>11a</jats:bold> was subjected to air oxidation, pyrazino[2',3':2,3;5',6':2,3]bis(5α-cholestane) (<jats:bold>9</jats:bold>) was obtained.</jats:p>
